---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const updated = '2026-07-02';
---

<BaseLayout title="Editorial Policy" description="How VisaLang researches, writes, and maintains guides." noindex={true}>
  <main class="page-shell">
    <article class="guide-article narrow-page">
        <p class="eyebrow">Editorial</p>
        <h1>Editorial Policy</h1>
        <p class="guide-summary">Last updated: {updated}</p>

        <h2>Our mission</h2>
        <p>VisaLang helps users find the right official language exam for visa, residency, citizenship, and work-registration paths. We point users to official sources rather than replacing them.</p>

        <h2>Official-first sourcing</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Every guide cites the official exam owner or government authority.</li>
          <li>We use blogs, forums, and third-party materials only for user-language context, never for factual requirements.</li>
          <li>We never invent fees, dates, accepted exams, or policy details.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What we do not publish</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Leaked exam questions or copied real exam items.</li>
          <li>Official logos presented in ways that imply endorsement.</li>
          <li>Guaranteed outcomes ("pass for sure", "visa approved").</li>
          <li>Specific fees, dates, or policy numbers without an official source.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Updates and accuracy</h2>
        <p>Every guide shows a Last Updated date. When official requirements change, we update guides and note the revision. If you spot an error, <a href="/contact/">tell us</a>.</p>

        <h2>Safe preparation</h2>
        <p>We only recommend original practice materials. We do not link to sites selling leaked questions or "guaranteed pass" shortcuts.</p>

        <h2>Commercial content</h2>
        <p>Affiliate links and sponsored prep recommendations appear only <em>after</em> the official-source section on a page, and are clearly labeled. See our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">Affiliate Disclosure</a>.</p>

        <h2>Independence</h2>
        <p>Editorial decisions are independent of any exam provider, school, or advertiser. No partner can edit our official-source guidance.</p>

        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
